{
  "_metadata": {
    "format_version": "1.0",
    "description": "LUMEN Film Stock Library — Parametric definitions for pipeline stages 5.5 through 10",
    "notes": [
      "Stage 5.5 (baseline_grading) sits between Camera Matrix (stage 5) and Film Model (stage 6)",
      "It applies a subtle camera-like rendering to all images before any stock is selected",
      "Stages 6-10 are the per-stock creative model",
      "All colour matrices are applied in scene-linear light",
      "Tone curve values define control points: input (scene linear 0-1) → output (density mapped 0-1)",
      "Hue shifts are in degrees, applied in HSL space",
      "Grain is composited in linear light, intensity scales with capture ISO when iso_responsive is true"
    ],
    "source_data": "Leica camera colour matrices from LibRaw/dcraw, Leica Look descriptions from leica-camera.com, M9 CCD analysis from multiple sources",
    "created": "2026-04-23",
    "author": "LUMEN research session"
  },

